{"reasoning":"The bug is that callers may provide camelCase flag names while the underlying dictionary uses snake_case keys, and the current implementation silently falls back to False on missing keys. I refactored the module to make the naming expectation explicit and added a small normalization helper so both camelCase and snake_case inputs resolve correctly. I also clarified the public API by documenting the accepted flag formats and preserving list_flags output as the canonical snake_case keys.","files":{"code_snippets_v2/silent_default_a/flags.py":""""Feature flag system with snake_case keys.

